<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="ida8510a31-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5" identifier="/us/usc/t10/s1048"><num value="1048">§ 1048.</num><heading> Gratuity payment to persons discharged for fraudulent enlistment</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Secretary concerned may pay a gratuity of not to exceed $25 to a person discharged for fraudulent enlistment.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="ida8510a32-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5">(Added <ref href="/us/pl/98/525/tXIV/s1401/d/1">Pub. L. 98–525, title XIV, § 1401(d)(1)</ref>, <date date="1984-10-19">Oct. 19, 1984</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/98/2616">98 Stat. 2616</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
